fava.functionable
Class FList<T>

java.lang.Object
  fava.functionable.Functionable<T>
      fava.functionable.FList<T>
Type Parameters:
T -
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>
public class FList<T>
extends Functionable<T>
implements java.util.List<T>

FList is a class which implements the List interface and acts as a pass-through to another list object. This allows FList to adopt any List implementation (eg Array, Linked). FList can imitate a sparse list's behaviour (although not runtime for sparse data) Eg. FList l = new FList(); l.add(4, "hello"); is a legitimate sequence of instructions, and will insert null values in the intervening elements.

Author:
Nathaniel Sherry
